  "instructions": [
    "Combine beets, pork belly, miso paste, soy sauce, rice vinegar, and honey in a bowl to make the filling. Wrap wonton wrappers around the filling, forming xiaolongbao. Bring a pot of water to a boil and blanch the xiaolongbao for 2 minutes. Preheat a charcoal grill to medium-high heat. Grill the xiaolongbao for 2-3 minutes, until charred and crispy. Remove from heat and garnish with scallions. Serve immediately."
